  "text": "In the last decades, metabolomics has developed at an amazing rate in the -omics field. At an early stage of development in the research of metabolic derivatives, biological generation method can be used; specifically, human and rat liver microsomes (HLMs & RLMs) were processed to investigate metabolites with specific cytochrome P450 (CYP450) activity [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . However, metabolites studied by HLM and RLM methods are expensive, time consuming, and labor intensive. Besides, under different conditions and extraction times, the results of HLM or RLM treatments will display different profiles in HLM and RLM metabolites [CITATION_5] .",
